WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.000
♪ Who's gonna help when the danger overwhelms ♪

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
♪ And the mysteries are piled high? ♪

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
♪ Who's gonna be around, never gonna let you down ♪

00:07.000 --> 00:09.000
♪ When you're on a wild ride? ♪

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ Your friends are always by your side ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:21.000 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
Mom! When are we gonna get to Grandma and Granddad's?

00:26.000 --> 00:29.000
"When you sit your behind back in that seat" o'clock.

00:29.000 --> 00:32.000
[ Whirring ] It's gonna be awesome,

00:32.000 --> 00:34.000
spending this 3-day weekend with my grandparents, y'all.

00:34.000 --> 00:37.000
Probably gonna work on some cool projects with my granddad.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.000
Neat.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.000
Well, me and the gang are just gonna go

00:40.000 --> 00:42.000
down the creek an-- Hold on a minute!

00:42.000 --> 00:43.000
If you guys are in my phone,

00:43.000 --> 00:44.000
who the heck are these guys?!

00:44.000 --> 00:45.000
[ English accent ] 'Ello, I'm Greg.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.000
My name's Chelsey.

00:46.000 --> 00:48.000
Hey, my name's Kelsey.

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
-And I'm Craig. -Really?!

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
Duane: We're here!

00:52.000 --> 00:54.000
Hey, baby! [chuckle]

00:54.000 --> 00:56.000
Here I come to get my sugar.

00:56.000 --> 00:58.000
Oh, you're lookin' so good, Jojo.

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
Hello, Madam Councilwoman.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.000
I'm off the clock,

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
so "Ma" will do just fine.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
Thanks for taking the kids this weekend, Ma.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.000
[ Smooch ]

01:07.000 --> 01:08.000
You know it's no trouble.

01:08.000 --> 01:10.000
I love gettin' in some quality time

01:10.000 --> 01:11.000
with my grandbabies.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.000
Grandma!

01:12.000 --> 01:15.000
Ooh. You're gettin' so big.

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
[laughs] I ate all my milk!

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
Hurry up and say hi!

01:19.000 --> 01:20.000
Quit pushin' me.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
You better gimme some sugar, Bernard.

01:22.000 --> 01:24.000
-[  Ding! ] Mwah. -[Laughing]

01:24.000 --> 01:25.000
You still gettin' good grades?

01:25.000 --> 01:27.000
Grandma, gimme some sugar, quick!

01:27.000 --> 01:28.000
[  Ding! ] Mwah!

01:29.000 --> 01:30.000
You always smell like outside.

01:30.000 --> 01:31.000
Where's Granddad?

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Oh, he's out in the garden.

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
Grandda-a-a-d!

01:35.000 --> 01:38.000
Those Williams men, always in a hurry.

01:38.000 --> 01:40.000
[ Engine starts ] Duane: Okay, Ma, gotta go.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
[ Tires squealing ] See you in a few days!

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
[ Suspenseful music plays ] Whoa!

01:44.000 --> 01:45.000
Granddad's garden.

01:46.000 --> 01:47.000
Earl: Another one?

01:47.000 --> 01:49.000
What could be doing this?

01:49.000 --> 01:52.000
[ Whimsical tune plays ]

01:52.000 --> 01:55.000
♪♪

01:55.000 --> 01:56.000
-Granddad! -Wha--?!

01:56.000 --> 01:59.000
[laughing] Hey, Craig.

01:59.000 --> 02:00.000
Check this out.

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
What the...? You ate a leaf?

02:02.000 --> 02:04.000
It wasn't me, Craig! Look.

02:04.000 --> 02:06.000
[ Gasp! ]

02:06.000 --> 02:07.000
[ Ominous music plays ] The eggplants!

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
Aah! The radishes!

02:10.000 --> 02:11.000
It can't be.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.000
[ Suspenseful music climbs ] Even the corn?!

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
Why?!

02:14.000 --> 02:15.000
Wait. What about the sweet potatoes?

02:16.000 --> 02:17.000
Now, now, now, don't worry.

02:17.000 --> 02:18.000
The sweet potatoes are safe.

02:18.000 --> 02:19.000
[ Sinister music plays ] For now.

02:19.000 --> 02:20.000
I just can't figure out

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
what's been eatin' everything.

02:22.000 --> 02:23.000
These bites are just too big

02:23.000 --> 02:25.000
to be a bug, or even a rodent.

02:25.000 --> 02:27.000
Well, whatever it is,

02:27.000 --> 02:29.000
we need to stop it.

02:29.000 --> 02:30.000
Mm-hmm!

02:30.000 --> 02:31.000
Sounds like a project.

02:31.000 --> 02:32.000
A project?

02:32.000 --> 02:34.000
Yep. To the workshop!

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
Hoh-hoh! The workshop!

02:36.000 --> 02:39.000
Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaah! -Agh. Agh. [Bones crackling]

02:39.000 --> 02:40.000
So you're sending these letters

02:41.000 --> 02:42.000
because you're constipated?

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
[laughs] I'm sending letters

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
to my constituents.

02:46.000 --> 02:47.000
That's what I said!

02:48.000 --> 02:49.000
Constipatients.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Oh, I see what's goin' on here, Miss Jessica.

02:51.000 --> 02:53.000
You're messin' with me.

02:53.000 --> 02:54.000
A little.

02:54.000 --> 02:55.000
Okay, Grandma.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.000
I got everything mixed, so far.

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
Should I put in the chocolate chips now?

02:58.000 --> 02:59.000
Chocolate chips?!

02:59.000 --> 03:01.000
Unh-unh! No, sir!

03:01.000 --> 03:03.000
In this house, we use

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
[ Ominous music plays ] chocolate chunks.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.000
Chocolate chunks?

03:07.000 --> 03:08.000
Why didn't I think of that

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
[ Suspenseful music climbs ] before?!

03:10.000 --> 03:12.000
Granddad and me are doing a project!

03:12.000 --> 03:14.000
I-I'm a-comin'. [ chuckle ]

03:14.000 --> 03:16.000
Hey, good-lookin'.

03:16.000 --> 03:17.000
Earl, you fresh.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.000
[ Click ]

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
Remember that spice rack we built

03:20.000 --> 03:21.000
last time I was here?

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
I made one just like it for the creek.

03:23.000 --> 03:25.000
Really? Now, that's impressive.

03:25.000 --> 03:28.000
We mainly use it to show off cool soda cans we find.

03:28.000 --> 03:29.000
Gotta show off those cans.

03:29.000 --> 03:31.000
Hey, what's this thing?

03:31.000 --> 03:34.000
Uh, that's what they call a seismograph.

03:34.000 --> 03:35.000
It was a retirement gift

03:35.000 --> 03:36.000
from the factory I used to work at.

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
What's it used for?

03:38.000 --> 03:39.000
Monster detection.

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
Monsters?! Really?!

03:41.000 --> 03:43.000
Uh, that, and earthquakes.

03:43.000 --> 03:44.000
Come on, grab a stool

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
and let's get this project started.

03:46.000 --> 03:47.000
[ Rattle ]

03:47.000 --> 03:48.000
[ Sproing ]

03:49.000 --> 03:50.000
[ Squeaking ]

03:50.000 --> 03:52.000
Okay, let's start with a simple layout

03:52.000 --> 03:53.000
and then -- -Can I give it a try?

03:53.000 --> 03:55.000
Sure, uh, t-t-take it away, Craig.

03:55.000 --> 03:57.000
Okay, here's your house.

03:57.000 --> 03:59.000
And here's the street we take

03:59.000 --> 04:01.000
to get to your house, past Duckmart.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.000
And I think Florida's down there, somewhere.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
And Europe is over here.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.000
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
back it up. Why don't we just make

04:09.000 --> 04:11.000
a simple map of the backyard?

04:11.000 --> 04:12.000
Like this.

04:12.000 --> 04:13.000
Yeah, I can see it.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
Let me just add one thing.

04:15.000 --> 04:16.000
[  Ding! ] There.

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
Now we have a visual reference for scale.

04:18.000 --> 04:21.000
So, how are we gonna go about protecting the garden?

04:21.000 --> 04:22.000
We can dig a moat around the yard [  Splash! ]

04:23.000 --> 04:25.000
and then fill it with flesh-eating piranhas!

04:25.000 --> 04:28.000
B-But what if this thing is piranhaproof?

04:28.000 --> 04:29.000
Oh. Good point.

04:29.000 --> 04:31.000
[ Eraser squeaks ] Wait!

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
Of course! How about a fence?!

04:33.000 --> 04:34.000
[ Metal clinking ] Hey, now,

04:34.000 --> 04:35.000
that's more like it.

04:35.000 --> 04:37.000
I got some spare wood in the shed

04:37.000 --> 04:38.000
and  lots of chicken wire layin' around.

04:38.000 --> 04:41.000
Because, see, we don't have any chickens, and so forth.

04:41.000 --> 04:43.000
But if we section off the whole garden,

04:43.000 --> 04:44.000
how are we gonna get inside?

04:44.000 --> 04:45.000
Oh, shoot! You're right.

04:45.000 --> 04:48.000
Maybe we could build one of them, umm --

04:48.000 --> 04:49.000
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, one of them,

04:49.000 --> 04:50.000
whatchamacallit --

04:50.000 --> 04:51.000
Oh, ooh, ooh.

04:51.000 --> 04:52.000
It kind of goes like this --

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
A-And it has one of these.

04:55.000 --> 04:56.000
A door!

04:56.000 --> 04:57.000
Yeah! A door! [laughs]

04:57.000 --> 04:59.000
Okay, lookin' good.

04:59.000 --> 05:01.000
Now, like they used to say at the old factory,

05:01.000 --> 05:02.000
Whoot!

05:02.000 --> 05:03.000
Wow!

05:03.000 --> 05:06.000
There. Got the chicken wire laid out.

05:06.000 --> 05:07.000
Now, to get my measuring tape

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
and carefully measure the exact length.

05:10.000 --> 05:11.000
Granddad! I finished putting

05:11.000 --> 05:12.000
the posts in the ground.

05:12.000 --> 05:14.000
Well, they're in the ground.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
At many different angles.

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
[ Thud ] Oh, sorry.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.000
Hey, don't worry about it.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.000
Patience is a skill that's hard to master.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
But when you're old, [Bones crackle] like me,

05:23.000 --> 05:26.000
agh, sometimes you have no choice but to be patient.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
Now, give this thing a nice, hard whack.

05:28.000 --> 05:31.000
[ Thudding ]

05:31.000 --> 05:34.000
[ Snapping ]

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
♪♪

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
[ Hinges squeaking ]

05:38.000 --> 05:40.000
There!

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Safe  and secure.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.000
[ Laughter, giggling ]

05:44.000 --> 05:46.000
Whoa, Grandma! Is that you?

05:46.000 --> 05:47.000
Sure is, Bernard.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
That's back when we still lived in the city.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
Jessica: Grandma, you look cool.

05:51.000 --> 05:54.000
Thank you, baby. [chuckle]

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
There was a lot goin' on back in those days.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.000
There's a lot goin' on right now.

05:59.000 --> 06:02.000
Nothing's getting through that fence.

06:02.000 --> 06:04.000
[ Birds chirping ]

06:04.000 --> 06:07.000
[ Clunk ] Sweet potatoes!

06:07.000 --> 06:08.000
Something tore up the fence!

06:08.000 --> 06:11.000
And my sweet potatoes!

06:11.000 --> 06:12.000
[ Hinge squeaks ]

06:12.000 --> 06:14.000
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
[crying] Poor little potato.

06:16.000 --> 06:19.000
Just two days from becoming a cobbler.

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
Well, whatever did this

06:21.000 --> 06:22.000
couldn't have come from the woods.

06:22.000 --> 06:25.000
This fence stretches around the whole neighborhood.

06:25.000 --> 06:26.000
[ Wind blowing ] And I doubt it was Gus.

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
We have an agreement.

06:28.000 --> 06:29.000
What could it be?

06:30.000 --> 06:31.000
Granddad, there's only one thing

06:31.000 --> 06:32.000
that could be eating the garden:

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
a monster.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
Hmm. I'm listening.

06:36.000 --> 06:37.000
Think about it. The creature would need

06:38.000 --> 06:40.000
to be able to shapeshift its way through the fence,

06:40.000 --> 06:42.000
[  Howling ] like a werewolf;

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
but only have a taste for vegetables,

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
like a vegan. [  Chomping, growling ]

06:47.000 --> 06:48.000
No doubt about it:

06:48.000 --> 06:49.000
a vegan werewolf is destroying our garden!

06:49.000 --> 06:52.000
Okay, well, I-I'd imagine catching a werewolf

06:53.000 --> 06:54.000
with dietary restrictions

06:54.000 --> 06:56.000
is much like catchin' any other vermin.

06:56.000 --> 06:57.000
With a trap! [Joints creak] Oh!

06:57.000 --> 06:59.000
Granddad, are you okay?

06:59.000 --> 07:00.000
G-Get Grandma.

07:00.000 --> 07:03.000
Earl, you gotta be careful

07:03.000 --> 07:04.000
not to overexert yourself.

07:04.000 --> 07:06.000
You know, if I had to choose

07:06.000 --> 07:09.000
between you and the corn, I'd choose you.

07:09.000 --> 07:10.000
Well, of course you would,

07:10.000 --> 07:11.000
because I come with the corn.

07:11.000 --> 07:13.000
We're a package deal.

07:13.000 --> 07:14.000
[ Sigh ]

07:14.000 --> 07:15.000
I just don't like being idle,

07:15.000 --> 07:17.000
doin' all this sittin' around.

07:17.000 --> 07:18.000
And I can't figure out

07:18.000 --> 07:20.000
what's happenin' out there.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.000
Well, maybe you can help me figure out

07:22.000 --> 07:24.000
where all this man's hair went.

07:24.000 --> 07:27.000
I sure did have nice hair.

07:27.000 --> 07:29.000
Looks like Granddad's out of commission.

07:29.000 --> 07:30.000
[ Birds chirping ]

07:30.000 --> 07:32.000
There's a monster in those woods.

07:32.000 --> 07:34.000
[ Suspenseful music plays ] I know it.

07:34.000 --> 07:37.000
I gotta stop it before it destroys the rest of the garden

07:37.000 --> 07:40.000
and everything Granddad holds dear.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.000
[ Click ]

07:42.000 --> 07:43.000
[ Sproing! ]

07:43.000 --> 07:44.000
[ Squeaking ]

07:44.000 --> 07:54.000
♪♪

07:54.000 --> 07:56.000
[ Owl hooting ] You're hunting monsters?!

07:56.000 --> 07:57.000
Tonight, me and my dad watched this movie

07:57.000 --> 07:59.000
where they turned the Empire State Building

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
into a missile and shot it at a monster.

08:01.000 --> 08:02.000
You thinking of doing something like that?

08:02.000 --> 08:04.000
I'm just using glue, for now.

08:04.000 --> 08:05.000
I'm hoping that's enough.

08:05.000 --> 08:07.000
This garden means a lot to my granddad.

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
But if it comes down to fighting a monster, I will.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.000
Ohh! I wish I was there.

08:12.000 --> 08:14.000
[ Fence rattling ] Huh?

08:14.000 --> 08:15.000
The monster!

08:15.000 --> 08:16.000
Be careful!

08:16.000 --> 08:18.000
Bring something to stab with!

08:18.000 --> 08:19.000
Have fun fightin' for your life!

08:19.000 --> 08:21.000
[ Hinge squeaks ] Huh?

08:21.000 --> 08:23.000
[ Wind blowing, crickets chirping ]

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
♪♪

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
[ Suspenseful music plays ] [ Cornstalks rustling ]

08:27.000 --> 08:28.000
Ha!

08:28.000 --> 08:29.000
[ Adventure music plays ]

08:29.000 --> 08:30.000
Aah-aah, unh!

08:30.000 --> 08:32.000
Whoa-whoa-whoa!

08:32.000 --> 08:33.000
Unh!

08:33.000 --> 08:35.000
It's gone!

08:35.000 --> 08:36.000
Unh!

08:36.000 --> 08:38.000
Grammy-y-y!

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
Earl: Well, I'd consider yourself lucky.

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
If it'd have been epoxy glue on that paper,

08:42.000 --> 08:44.000
you'd be dressin' like a mummy

08:44.000 --> 08:45.000
every Halloween for the rest of your life.

08:45.000 --> 08:47.000
Not to mention every other day of the year.

08:47.000 --> 08:48.000
I know.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
Ow! Jessica!

08:50.000 --> 08:53.000
You wanna walk around all day, lookin' silly?!

08:53.000 --> 08:55.000
Well, I don't know if it's safe

08:55.000 --> 08:57.000
to be playin' with traps, in the first place.

08:57.000 --> 08:58.000
Both: It would've worked!

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
If he hadn't rushed out there.

09:00.000 --> 09:01.000
I'm just sayin'.

09:01.000 --> 09:03.000
You Williams boys are always in a rush.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.000
You  need to be patient.

09:05.000 --> 09:07.000
Right.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.000
[ Click ]

09:09.000 --> 09:13.000
[ Adventure music plays ]

09:13.000 --> 09:15.000
No more tricks. No more traps.

09:16.000 --> 09:19.000
I'm just gonna sit here and wait for the monster.

09:19.000 --> 09:20.000
[ Birds chirping ]

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
And maybe have a cookie.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.000
[ Crunching ]

09:24.000 --> 09:25.000
Ugh! Bernard.

09:25.000 --> 09:29.000
[ Eerie music plays ]

09:29.000 --> 09:30.000
[ Leaves rustle, branch snaps ] [ Gasp! ]

09:30.000 --> 09:32.000
[ Crickets chirping ]

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
Wh-who's there?

09:34.000 --> 09:35.000
[ Rustling ]

09:35.000 --> 09:38.000
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

09:38.000 --> 09:48.000
♪♪

09:48.000 --> 09:51.000
♪♪

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
[ Whoosh! ] [ Gasp! ]

09:53.000 --> 09:54.000
[ Munch ]

09:54.000 --> 09:56.000
♪♪

09:56.000 --> 09:58.000
H-How did you get in here?

09:59.000 --> 10:00.000
Whah! Ooh!

10:01.000 --> 10:02.000
Wait! Don't go!

10:03.000 --> 10:04.000
[ Whimsical-suspenseful tune ] [ Panting ]

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
Huah! Unh!

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
Ah! Oof!

10:09.000 --> 10:11.000
Slow down, speedy!

10:11.000 --> 10:12.000
What?

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
[ Fence rattling ] There's a hole in the fence.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
That's how you've been getting in and out.

10:16.000 --> 10:19.000
♪♪

10:19.000 --> 10:20.000
Hey, it's okay.

10:20.000 --> 10:22.000
I'm not gonna hurt ya.

10:22.000 --> 10:24.000
[ Grunting ]

10:24.000 --> 10:27.000
Mnh-ohh!

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
[ Tender tune plays ]

10:30.000 --> 10:34.000
♪♪

10:34.000 --> 10:35.000
[ Leaves rustle ]

10:35.000 --> 10:37.000
I'm gonna make a call

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
to the City Bureau of Fence Services

10:39.000 --> 10:40.000
and have them come down and check

10:40.000 --> 10:43.000
if there are any more holes that need to be patched.

10:43.000 --> 10:46.000
That's City Councilwoman Grandma Williams.

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
[ Thudding ]

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
Thanks for solving the mystery, Craig.

10:51.000 --> 10:52.000
Whoa!

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
Now the Deer Goddess owes you one.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
I'll have to call it in on my next adventure

10:56.000 --> 10:59.000
at my grandparents' house.

10:59.000 --> 11:00.000
-Bye-bye, now! -Bye!

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
All right, we miss you already.

11:02.000 --> 11:05.000
♪ When it's time to go to bed ♪

11:05.000 --> 11:09.000
♪ I know I don't have to feel alone ♪

11:09.000 --> 11:13.000
♪ 'Cause I'll see you tomorrow ♪

11:13.000 --> 11:14.000
♪ At the creek ♪

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Just like I drew it.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
♪♪
